This program counts the number of digits present in an integer. A while loop repeatedly divides the number by 10. Each division removes one digit from the number.
[ C++ Practice Test ]
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;int main() {
int num = 987654;
int count = 0;
while (num != 0) {
count++;
num /= 10;
}
cout << "Number of Digits = " << count;
return 0;
}
Output :
Number of Digits = 6
